text=(:Summary: Some of the many wonderful places where PmWiki is ''successfully'' used:)%0aHere are a few sites that are using [[PmWiki/]] to successfully meet their web needs (also see [[PmWiki/references]], [[PmWiki Users]], [[PmWiki Friendly Hosting]]).%0a-%3c Have your own success story to share?  Add it below!  [-(Did PmWiki ''not'' work for you?  Add it to [[Failure Stories]]!)-]%0a%0a[-This list is sorted alphabetically, please add your site accordingly.-]%0a%0a(:notoc:)%0a%25center%25 [[#digits|0-9]] [[#A|A]] [[#B|B]] [[#C|C]] [[#D|D]] [[#E|E]] [[#F|F]] [[#G|G]] [[#H|H]] [[#I|I]] [[#J|J]] [[#K|K]] [[#L|L]] [[#M|M]] [[#N|N]] [[#O|O]] [[#P|P]] [[#Q|Q]] [[#R|R]] [[#S|S]] [[#T|T]] [[#U|U]] [[#V|V]] [[#W|W]] [[#XYZ|XYZ]]%0a%0a!-0-9-[[#digits]]%25center%25%0a----%0a%25lfloat margin-right:10px%25 [[http://175g.ru/wiki/Teams/CosmicGirls|Attach:175g-ru.jpg]]%0a!!![[(http://)175g.ru/wiki]]%0a175g.ru is intended to collect and structure experience of Russian-speaking Ultimate frisbee players.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a----%0a!!![[(https://)5ko.fr]]%0aThe personal website of [[~Petko]], the core developer of PmWiki (in French; some sections are password-protected). %0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a!-A-[[#A]]%25center%25%0a%0a----%0a%25lfloat margin-right:10px%25  [[http://www.aardwolf.com/wiki | http://www.aardwolf.com/img/aard_wiki_thumb.jpg]]%0a%0a!!![[http://www.aardwolf.com/wiki/ | Aardwolf MUD]]%0aAardwolf is a large multiplayer game online since 1996 with hundreds of commands and player abilities.%0a%0aPMWiki has been a fantastic tool for organizing our game data and allowing players to share information with others.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a%0a%25lfloat margin-right:10px%25  [[http://abundantlifefarm.com/ | http://eclectichosting.net/portfolio/AbundantLifeFarm-crop-thumb.jpg]]%0a%0a(:table margin-left=10px border=1 width=30%25 align=right bgcolor=#ccffff cellspacing=0 :)%0a(:cellnr:)%0a'''[[http://eclectictech.net/ | Eclectic Tech site]]'''\\%0a[[~XES | by The Crisses]]%0a(:cellnr:)%0a*Blog%0a*Calendar%0a*Joins with Zen Cart site%0a*Design by Silverflux Design%0a(:tableend:)%0a%0a!!![[http://abundantlifefarm.com/ | Abundant Life Farm, Middletown, NY]]%0aOffers childrens programs, harvest and other festivals, biodynamic spraying services and now localvore farm product delivery service (via ZenCart) to drop-off points in the region.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a%0a!!!!'''[[http://www.aaai.org/AITopics|AI Topics]]'''%0a%0a%25lfloat margin-right:10px%25  [[http://www.aaai.org/AITopics | http://www.aaai.org/aitopics/pmwiki/pub/images/homepageScreenshot.JPG]]%0aAITopics is a virtual library of resources for students, teachers, journalists, and everyone who would like to learn about artificial intelligence. By offering a limited number of exemplary, non-technical resources that we have organized and annotated, AI Topics seeks to provide visitors with meaningful access to basic, understandable information about AI.%0a%0aAITopics uses PMWiki to organize, and archive content, as well as to facilitate working in an environment with many editors.%0a%0a[[http://www.aaai.org/AITopics]] %0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a!!!!Amnesty International Germany%0a%25lfloat%25Attach:amnesty_germany_groupshot.jpg%0aAmnesty International Germany is using pmwiki in various ways within the organization successfully for the last three years. It is in use on about 100 websites of regional groups of activists. The organization therefor created an easy to install package that is also easy to maintain. This preconfigured package is updated every few weeks and has seen many updates by now. It cherrypicked recipes that are very useful for regional activists. The weblayout was designed by a professional design agency and implemented for pmwiki by volunteer activists.%0a%0aMoreover pmwiki is used for the administration of the annual meeting of the whole organization in Germany.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a!!!!A.M.O.K.%0a%25lfloat width=160px%25http://amok.wtf/uploads/AMOK/amkoscrn.png%0a[[http://amok.wtf|Amok]] is an informal artists-run workshop, hackerspace & gallery based in Aarhus, Denmark.[[%3c%3c]]%0aPmWiki is the perfect choice for quick and collectively designed, organic website. %0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a!!!! `ApfelWiki.de%0a%0a%25lfloat%25 [[http://www.apfelwiki.de | Attach:ApfelWikiSShot.png]]%0aApfelwiki is a german project trying to build up a reference about working with Apple Computer like a large FAQ. The only way to let the user create their own pages was a wiki. But we won't have the same "old fashioned" wiki-look. So we decided to take pmwiki. It's a powerful wiki and with css we made a modern layout. Last but not least pmwiki is very easy to handle.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a!!!![[http://nonmarchand.org|Association pour les échanges non-marchands et la culture libre (ANOMALI)]]%0a%25lfloat margin-right:10px%25  [[http://nonmarchand.org/ | http://nonmarchand.org/Fichiers/Anomali.jpg]]%0aAnomali is a non profit organization which promotes non market economy and free culture. We developed a tool for network exchange with pmwiki.%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a!!!!Audi100.Selbst-Doku.de%0a'''Website: http://audi100.selbst-doku.de'''%0a%0aThe Audi100.Selbst-Doku.de is a german/english self documentation site regarding the Audi 100 (type44, C4) and A6 cars. It's users have collected 500+ detailed topics explaining repairs and improvements covering almost every single aspect of the cars. (Body, paint, steering, engine and tuning, drivetrain, lighting, electronic motor management and so on).%0a%0aFirst running PhpWiki it was sucessfully migrated to PmWiki 2.x a few months ago (yehawww! :) ) and features a lot of the cockbook extensions to suit it's user's needs.%0aThanks so much for the well documented, easy to run and feature rich software, PmWiki has become!%0aAxel Groll%0aMunich :) %0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a%0a%0a%25lfloat margin-right:10px%25  [[http://archutech.com/ | http://eclectichosting.net/portfolio/archutech.com-thumb.jpg]]%0a%0a(:table margin-left=10px border=1 width=30%25 align=right bgcolor=#ccffff cellspacing=0 :)%0a(:cellnr:)%0a'''[[http://eclectictech.net/ | Eclectic Tech site]]'''\\%0a[[~XES | by The Crisses]]%0a(:cellnr:)%0a*Joins with OSTicket%0a*dynamic content features%0a*Design & logo by Eclectic Tech%0a(:tableend:)%0a%0a!!![[http://archutech.com/ | Archutech Consulting, Bronx, NY]]%0aArchutech consulting offers PC and network services in NYC and Westchester, NY.  Client wanted partial integration with OSTicket for clients to submit trouble tickets.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a'''[=AzRepeaters.Net=]: Arizona Repeaters on 6, 2 , & 1.25 Meters 70, 33, & 23 Centimeters Bands''' (http://www.azrepeaters.net) %0a%0a%25lfloat%25 [[http://www.azrepeaters.net/azrepeatersnetscreen.png ->http://www.azrepeaters.net]] %0aIn 2004, my brother Tom passed away in a tragic accident. His legacy included a sited dedicated to helping Hams in Arizona find repeaters in the state.\\%0aThis is important as it is used by the Red Cross and other emergency agencies to help assist people in need.\\%0a%0aNot being a Ham myself, I was faced with the daunting task of how to keep it going and allowing experts to keep the site up to date. The answer for me was found at a [[http://www.ntlug.org | Northern Texas Linux Users Group ]] meeting where Patrick Michaud talked about this great Wiki project he was heading up. I knew I had found the solution to keeping my brother's dream alive.\\%0a%0aWith the advanced tables function and some sed and grep scripts, I was able to quickly convert much of my brother's site over a weekend. It went live just before Labor Day 2005. I still have more work to do, but now, Arizona Hams and other Hams have the ability to keep the site up to date instantly.\\%0a%0aNow I have many Hams who keep the site up for me without my having to directly make the edits myself as I did before I went Wiki. Apparently, according to one of my editors, he has become a celeb in the Ham community. And it is so easy for him to make edits too!%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a!-B-[[#B]]%25center%25%0a----%0a'''beckos Tabletop Site''' (http://becko.tabletop-minis.de)%0a%0a%25lfloat width=250px%25 [[http://becko.tabletop-minis.de/banner/beckos_tabletop_site.jpg ->http://becko.tabletop-minis.de]]%0a%0a[[http://becko.tabletop-minis.de/|beckos Tabletop Site]] is a personal homepage about wargaming and miniature painting. Becky paints armies and dioramas since several years. The main tabletop systems on the site are Warhammer 40k, Warhammer Fantasy Battles, Flames of War and Battlefleet Gothic. The Imperial Guard of Armageddon is the main project for the year 2009/10. Since the start of the website in 2005 PmWiki is the engine he uses to announce news and pictures about his hobby. [[~Becko]]%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a'''Jan Brejcha // Interaction design''' (http://jan.brejcha.name)%0a%0a%25lfloat width=250px%25 http://jan.brejcha.name/gallery/brejcha.png%0a%0a[[http://jan.brejcha.name | Jan Brejcha // Interaction design]] is a personal and professional homepage of an Interaction Design practitioner and lecturer. He creates web-sites using PmWiki as a CMS. Used PmWiki for the redesign of an HTML-based page enabling a more comfortable and faster content editing, multi-language support, Picasa web-gallery and global navigation. Author: [[~JanBrejcha]]%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a'''Bendigo Gliding Club''' (http://www.bendigogliding.org.au)%0a%0a%25lfloat%25 http://www.bendigogliding.org.au/uploads/Main/gliding-screenshot.jpg%0a%0a[[http://www.bendigogliding.org.au | Bendigo Gliding Club]] is a small community based gliding club in Victoria, Australia.  Most of the club members are tech savvy spending all manner of time paying with fancy flying electronics and flight loggers, however, HTML, Javascript and web editing is a very different technical domain!  PmWiki was the ideal solution for the club. It offered simple editing, version control and the ability to implement a password protected &#8220;members only&#8221; section.  The key to PmWiki&#8217;s success is its separation of simplicity and power &#8211; that is power to the administrator and simplicity for the content authors.  The administrators (the ones needing the power) are the tech guys at [[http://www.papercut.com/ | PaperCut Software]] who were kind enough to donate their server resources and time, and the authors are the &#8220;simpler&#8221; guys at the gliding club.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a%0a%0a----%0a'''bilder-gucken.net''' (http://www.bilder-gucken.net)%0a%0a%25lfloat%25[[http://www.bilder-gucken.net| Attach:bilder-gucken-net-screen.jpg]]%0aThis german website is about my offer of tarot readings. It is aimed at customers interested in getting a reading as well as people who wish to study the art and seek instructions.  There is a list of services and a collection of my texts on tarot and divination. The site uses a slightly customized [[Skins/Not so simple]] skin.%0a%0aI'm using a wiki because I want to be able to easily update the site from everywhere. I selected PmWiki for it's great maintainability, it's small footprint and because it's really easy to customize. It was a breeze to set up all the features I want on the site. Thank you, Pm, for your work and thank you everyone for your contributions!%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a'''binaervarianz Kletterwiki''' http://klettern.binaervarianz.de%0a%0a%25lfloat%25 [[http://klettern.binaervarianz.de|http://people.freenet.de/chaos99/kletterwiki_screen.png]]%0aThis german wiki focuses on sports- and mountain-climbing and adresses beginners as well as anyone interested in%0aclimbing at all. It lists and reviews climbing spots and halls in Germany and offers a place to meet and share experiences.%0a%0aWe used a wiki in general to be able to make adjustments to the pages even "on the road" from every computer without much effort or even html-knowledge. Also, as an open wiki, everybody should be able to add content to the site without worrying about ''how'' to do so. PMWiki was a slim and elegant way to get this, and we used it before as part of our main page [[http://www.binaervarianz.de]].%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a----%0a%25lfloat%25[[http://budcare.org/kids/ | http://budcare.org/zimages/budcarelogo.png]]%0a'''Budcare.org''', is a %25red%25free website in pediatrics and neonatology for health care students and professionals%25%25, to access quick reviews, latest news, abstracts, audio-video content, clinical calculators and others. For more, visit http://budcare.org.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a----%0a'''BU130 Trui'''%0a%25lfloat%25 [[http://www.bu130.nl|http://www.bu130.nl/bu130.nl.png]]%0aThe Trui is an old dutch fishing ship completely restored and sailed by students of the Delft University of Technology. Here PmWiki is used as a base for the regular website and as a system to record all important data about the ship, her maintenance and an almanac of the waters she sails. Running a customised version of the Flexi skin, incorporating tabs and custom styles.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a----%0a%25lfloat margin-right:10px%25  [[http://bizxnet.info/ | http://eclectichosting.net/portfolio/bizxnet.info3-thumb.jpg]]%0a%0a(:table margin-left=10px border=1 width=30%25 align=right bgcolor=#ccffff cellspacing=0 :)%0a(:cellnr:)%0a'''[[http://eclectictech.net/ | Eclectic Tech site]]'''\\%0a[[~XES | by The Crisses]]%0a(:cellnr:)%0a*Member-only login area%0a*MySQL database member logins%0a*Business Directory%0a*Calendar%0a*Member profiles%0a*Logo by Eclectic Tech%0a(:tableend:)%0a%0a!!![[http://bizxnet.info/ | Business Exchange Network, Middletown, NY]]%0aThis is a referral-based networking group in Orange County, NY.  The website features per-member directory & category entries, and a networking calendar for both internal and external local events.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a%25lfloat margin-right:10px%25  [[http://bpwmiddletownny.org/ | http://eclectichosting.net/portfolio/bpwmiddletownny.org-thumb.jpg]]%0a%0a(:table margin-left=10px border=1 width=30%25 align=right bgcolor=#ccffff cellspacing=0 :)%0a(:cellnr:)%0a'''[[http://eclectictech.net/ | Eclectic Tech site]]'''\\%0a[[~XES | by The Crisses]]%0a(:cellnr:)%0a*Member-only area with directory%0a*Design ported%0a(:tableend:)%0a%0a!!![[http://bpwmiddletownny.org/ | Middletown Business & Professional Women Club, Middletown, NY]]%0aI've just taken over as the website chairperson of the club, and the website has been ported, new features are being added.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a%0a!-C-[[#C]]%25center%25%0a%0a----%0a%0a'''CIIP Wiki'''  %0a%0a%0a%25lfloat width=390px%25 [[http://www.ciip4me.com/wiki/ | http://www.ciip4me.com/images/logor.png]]%0a%0a%0aA wiki site, set up and created for interns of The Cisco International Internship Program to share information and experiences.%0a%0a%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a%0a'''Campusradio Jena - the local radio stations for the inhabitants of Jena produced by well motiated students'''  %0a%0a%0a%25lfloat width=390px%25 [[http://www.campusradio-jena.de | http://www.wikimatze.de/pmwiki/uploads/Code/Code/campusradio_jena.png]]%0a%0a%0aThis website was created with the purpose to be easy maintain, migrate and to add the possibility to provide quickly new updates. This stub of the page was created with the blueprint css framework so the appearance is nearly the same in most browsers out there. Another important think was the integration of the mp3-files: For that I used the great [[Cookbook/FlashMediaPlayer | Flash Media Player recipe]].%0a%0aOf course, there are several other usefull recipes which are in usage:%0a%0a* [[Cookbook/PageTableOfContents | TOC]], [[Cookbook/SectionEdit | SectionEdit]], [[Cookbook/RowspanInSimpleTables | Simple Tables]]%0a* [[Cookbook/Bloge | Bloge]], [[Cookbook/DeObMail| DeObMail]], [[/Cookbook/Mini | Mini]]%0a* [[Cookbook/Twitter | Twitter]], [[Cookbook/CommentBoxPlus | Comment Box Plus]]%0a%0aOther things like webcam or playlist were directly integrated via plain html because the technology for this was already present%0a%0a-> Link: [[http://www.campusradio-jena.de]]%0a%0a->''[[~MatthiasGünther]] April 05, 2010, at 08:39 AM''%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a%0a'''clockwise consulting'''%0a%0a%25lfloat width=390px%25 [[http://www.clockwise-consulting.de | http://www.wikimatze.de/pmwiki/uploads/Code/Code/clockwise_consulting.png]]%0a%0a%0aThis website was created to simply display the ideas and concerns of this consulting firm based in Jena. Again the blueprint css framework was used to create the basic layout. There were no special recipes used and the bulk part of the work was spend in the navigation and clean structure of the website.%0a%0a-> Link: [[http://www.clockwise-consulting.de]]%0a%0a%0a->''[[~MatthiasGünther]] November 07, 2010, at 6:30 PM''%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a%0a%0a'''Ciessetrade ''' (http://ciessetrade.cz)%0a%0a%25lfloat width=250px%25 http://jan.brejcha.name/gallery/commercial.png%0a%0a[[http://ciessetrade.cz | Ciessetrade]] is a commercial homepage of a machine-tool trade company. It uses PmWiki as a back-end CMS. Used PmWiki for a more comfortable and faster content editing and global navigation. (Designer: [[http://jan.brejcha.name|Jan Brejcha]]).  Author: [[~JanBrejcha]]%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a%0a%0a'''Classic Science Fiction And Fantasy''' (http://classic-sf.com)%0a%0a%25lfloat%25 [[http://www.classic-sf.co.uk|http://www.classic-sf.co.uk/images/csf.jpg]]%0a%0aA one-stop database of information about science fiction and fantasy stories, writers etc.%0a%0aI got fed up of jumping from site to site to book to site etc. etc. to get information I wanted. So, starting with  the books I have at home I started my database.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a----%0a'''clickMarlow.co.uk''' ( http://clickmarlow.co.uk/ )%0a%0a%25lfloat%25[[http://clickmarlow.co.uk/|Attach:clickmarlow.jpg]] %0aFinally adopted [=PmWiki=] as the CMS of choice and to great effect. Once the templating system is mastered then quite sophisticated sites can be made. I love the speed, love the programmability and also to limit clients the use of just headline, '''bold''' and ''italic''. %0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a %0a----%0a!!!Congregation Bat-Tzion [[%3c%3c]][--A Messianic Jewish Congregation--]%0a%0a%25lfloat%25[[http://www.battzion.org | http://battzion.org/cbt/pmwiki/uploads/Site/Logo/logo.png]]%25%25%0a%25justify%25Come and learn about Yeshua HaMashiach our Jewish Messiah and Son of Yahu'ah - who he really is and what he really came to do.  Based upon the Jewish Bible and explained by Jewish descendants, these are many times contrary to what the world teaches.  Come to a solid Biblical foundation of understanding which is not fettered by the ties of Talmudic teachings which sometimes stray from the Torah in understanding due to the commentary of men between the %25newwin%25[[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hillel_and_Shammai | Houses of Hillel and Shammai]]%25%25, Constantine-style teachings which have infiltrated and corrupted the Messianic teachings with pagan practices, or any other ways and teachings that reach into the depths of Bavel (Babylon, also: confusion) or Mitzraim (Egypt, also: double-trouble).%25%25%0a%0a%25center%25"Who has established all the ends of the earth?  What is His Name, and what is His Son's Name?  For you will know it..."[[%3c%3c]] מִי הֵקִים כָּל-אַפְסֵי אָרֶץ; מַה שְּׁמוֹ וּמַה שֶּׁם בְּנוֹ, כִּי תֵדָע [[%3c%3c]]Mishley (Proverbs) 30:4%25%25%0a%0a%25justify%25The PmWiki project has been a wonderful tool of organization and framework of learning.  The ease of multi-layered security structure and handling, as well as the ability to customize plug-ins or create specialized directives is just what was needed for a congregation to be fully dynamic and functional in the online world.  The ability to customize CSS-loaded web-font kits and page document structures is truly remarkable in the way it assists to complete the feel of desired effects considering the times and information being addressed.  The WebMaster of this site has truly not seen many other project forums that provide for the depth of detail, work-ability, configuration, and dynamic plug-in morphing structure that the PmWiki project provides.%25%25%0a%0a----%0a'''Corpus Christi Downtown Management District'''%0a%0a%25lfloat%25[[http://www.downtowncorpuschristi.com | http://thunderdata.com/uploads/Main/dmd4.jpg]]%0aThe [[http://www.downtowncorpuschristi.com |Downtown Management District]] is a non-profit organization aimed at improving the quality of life in the downtown Corpus Christi.  This site, after only 2 days, has generated a lot of enthusiatic support including an article in the city's [[http://www.caller.com/ccct/business/article/0,1641,CCCT_873_2422057,00.html|newspaper]].  It addressed several issues that has hampered the growth of downtown including communication among members of the comunity and the DMD, housing and quality of life issues, arts, history and tourist information, as well as a voice for direction.  We feel that the site is so well tailored to PmWiki and they agree!%0a%0a''Dawn Green, [[http://www.thunderdata.com|Thunder Data Systems, Inc]]''%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a----%0a'''Corpus Christi International Competition For Piano And Strings, Inc.'''%0a%0a%25lfloat%25 [[http://webprose.cc/portfolio_pics/ccic_small.jpg->http://ccicps.org]]%25%25 [[Corpus Christi International Competition For Piano and Strings, Inc.->http://ccicps.org]] is a widely recognized competition open to students of the piano, violin, viola, cello, double bass or harp who are under the age of 26.  This small non-profit organization required a website ''they'' can update to distribute information to prospective participants.  Within one day of the site going live, the President of the organization was making significant changes to the site.  PmWiki wins again!%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a----%0a'''Corpus Christi Linux Users Group''' (http://www.cclug.org)%0a%0a%25lfloat%25 [[http://www.cclug.org |PmImg:2003/cclug-1.gif]]%0aPrior to using PmWiki, the CCLUG web site was frequently out of date and difficult to update.  All changes to the site had to be coordinated through the organization's webmaster, who was responsible for linking in new content and web pages (on a volunteer basis, of course).  But with PmWiki, now all of CCLUG's members can participate in building the site!  Visitors to the site can quickly find what's new via the [[http://www.cclug.org/wiki/Main/RecentChanges |site's RecentChanges]] page, and members can quickly and easily add new content.  It's a whole new way for organizations to build and maintain web sites!%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a----%0a'''Corpus Christi Literary Reading Series'''%0a%0a%25lfloat%25 [[http://webprose.cc/screen/literary.png-> http://www.literaryreadingseries.com]]%0aThese clients wanted something that would allow them to have dialogue between members as well as promote future speakers.  They also wanted a website that would allow them to be able to acquire more sponsors by having web page addition as part of their reportoire of marketing tactics for pursuing corporate sponsorship.  Just so happened, Wiki fit the bill perfectly here too.  Set them up, make sure they like the "design" of the site, get some initial information from them, then tutor them on how wiki works.  Its a no lose situation, and is making web content addition for non-html'ers and even non computer people easy.%0a%0a''---Created by:[[The Webprose Team->http://www.webprose.cc]]''%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a----%0a%25lfloat margin-right:10px%25  [[http://crollorganizing.com/ | http://eclectichosting.net/portfolio/crollorganizing.com-thumb.jpg]]%0a%0a(:table margin-left=10px border=1 width=30%25 align=right bgcolor=#ccffff cellspacing=0 :)%0a(:cellnr:)%0a'''[[http://eclectictech.net/ | Eclectic Tech site]]'''\\%0a[[~XES | by The Crisses]]%0a(:cellnr:)%0a*Custom registration form for seminars%0a*Blog%0a*Audio content%0a*Design ported from A&E Advertising%0a(:tableend:)%0a%0a!!![[http://crollorganizing.com/ | Croll Organizing, LLC, Westtown, NY]]%0aProfessional organizer and speaker, Cynthia Marsh-Croll wanted to be able to change her own content, and have new dynamic features added to her website.  She eventually plans to sell audio or video seminars from her website.%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a%0a!-D-[[#D]]%25center%25%0a----%0a'''Dausha Publications''' (http://dausha.net/)%0a%0aThe official website of writer Ben Wilson,%0aco-creator of the EverySpace milieu and Science Fiction novelist. %0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a----%0a'''[[https://www.dr-toolbox.com|Dr Toolbox]]'''%0a%0aCreated and maintained by [[~Petko]], the core developer of PmWiki. A platform and a mobile app in the UK helping medical professionals share practical information about their work locally, with their team in their hospital.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a%0a----%0a'''DST Output: Customer Systems'''%0a%0aWe've started using PmWiki to do organic documentation generation.  It's been very useful in allowing a largish group of individuals to contribute to living documents.  The benefit is that the live documentation is always up-to-date and no changes are ever lost, unlike email chains and word docs.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a'''Online Dutch Grammar Course'''%0a%0a[[http://www.dutchgrammar.com/en/ | Dutchgrammar.com]] is a website for people who are studying Dutch. It has a grammar reference, exercises, audio files, a Learn Dutch podcast, and a forum. I wrote the original grammar reference in English and Dutch learners have been translating the pages into their own languages. I used to receive text documents, which took me ages to process. PmWiki made everything wonderfully easy. Translators can now log in and translate the pages without my intervention. I think PmWiki is a great CMS. %0a%0aThe tutorial for translators can be found [[http://www.dutchgrammar.com/en/index.php?n=Translators.GettingStarted | here]]%0a%0a%0a!-E-[[#E]]%25center%25%0a----%0a'''ecolog'^ee^'net'''%0a%0a%25lfloat newwin%25[[http://www.ecologee.net | http://www.ecologee.net/uploads/Service/ecologee_250_180.png]]%0a'''ecolog'^ee^'net''' is the starting point for ecologic - internet solutions. As the internet-based technology  makes the fastest growing consumer of electric power worldwide, we have to develop different solutions to cut the www's energy consumption down. We all love the internet, but it turns out that we can harm ourself. PmWiki is the natural choice for a typical development environment for ideas and a spot where developers can easily meat each other.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a----%0a'''www.ello.uos.de'''%0a%25lfloat newwin%25[[http://www.ello.uos.de|http://zentrum.virtuos.uos.de/wikifarm/fields/english-language/uploads/Main/Ello_screenshot.jpg]]%0aELLO (English Language and Linguistics Online) is a modular introductory courseware in English linguistics developed by a linguistic-department network of 4 German universities: Osnabrück, Hannover, Braunschweig and Göttingen. The website is designed as a study aid for undergraduate students of linguistics and consists of 15 modules covering courseware on general linguistics as well as on selected subfields.%0a%0aComplex material is created and stored in a PmWiki which also allows the integration of interactive exercises and multimedia content, including audio and video material of all kinds.%0aProf. Dr. Alexander Bergs is the founding father and manager of ELLO%0a%0aLook at: http://www.ello.uni-osnabrueck.de/%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a----%0a%0a'''Elysian Fields''' (http://faroah.com)%0a%0a%25lfloat%25 http://i6.photobucket.com/albums/y235/freesong_adoptables/ef1.gif %25%25 Elysian Fields is a play-by-post forum-based roleplaying game set in a vast, unique and original fantasy setting. We use PmWiki's software to host our static information so that our members can submit content and help develop and evolve the world in which we play. We're a fun and friendly community who just love to RP!%0a%0a----%0a%0a'''Encyclopédie du paranormal''' (http://www.paranormal-encyclopedie.com)%0a%0a%25lfloat  newwin %25 [[http://www.paranormal-encyclopedie.com|http://www.paranormal-e