ki [[http://lbts.usc.es|our main website]] abandoning other authoring packages which, though commercial and widely used, did not provide us the trouble-free experience that PmWiki delivers. Our University has rather strict style guidelines for the visual appearance of departmental webs, and so we were pleased to discover how easy and flexible is to customize PmWiki's appearance.  We are also delighted with the reasonably direct support of mathematical formulas, greek letters, accented characters... and how all the formatings look ''automagically'' OK in all browsers. Now '''that's''' trouble-free! Our site is designed to not appear as a wiki to outside visitors, with the edit access (restricted to lab members) provided as a line of "administration" links at the bottom of the site; this is virtually unnoticed by outside visitors, yet is comfortably found by the lab people. %0a%0aOther sites of our university have migrated to PmWiki after this successful experience, using similar templates, including some [[http://www.usc.es/cond-mat|departmental sites]], [[http://www.usc.es/posgrao/materiais|master degree sites]], [[http://lbts.usc.es/wikidocente|student wiki sites]], research group sites [[http://chaos.usc.es|like]] [[http://www.usc.es/gnmmb|these]] [[http://lbts.usc.es/ramallo|ones]], etc. %0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a----%0a%0a%25lfloat text-align=left margin-top=15px margin-right=25px margin-bottom=15px margin-left=5px width=200px%25  [[http://www.montpellier-informatique.com/blog/ | http://www.montpellier-informatique.com/ico/blogscreenshot200px.png]]%0a!!!! Le Blog de Montpellier-Informatique.com\\%0a[[http://www.montpellier-informatique.com/blog/|http://www.montpellier-informatique.com/blog/]]%0aA blog about PHP programming, in french language.\\%0a''It took me one afternoon to setup this blog with Pmwiki. The CommentBoxPlus recipe proved to be very handy.''\\%0a(12-2008)%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a----%0a%0a!!!! Les débroussailleuses ( [[http://lesdebroussailleuses.org]] )%0a%0