ined. Defiantly going to use PmWiki for future sites. %0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a!-M-[[#M]]%25center%25%0a%0a----%0a'''M-Horton Clothing Design'''  %0a%0aPowerful enough to attract hits from the Maldives, and easy enough for a seamstress to "get it" and do-it-herself! Next on the list is integrating the social networking site buttons and adding PayPal support. This has been a wonderful experience to dive into the open-source community. I modified the tag on the bottom of the site to say "Open-Source and Fancy-Free with PmWiki" I LOVE my website.\\\%0aThanks to everyone in the PmWiki community!\\\%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a--------%0a'''Map uit - Xiao-o Wiki''' ([[http://www.mapuit.com]]) %0a%0a%25lfloat%25 [[http://www.mapuit.com|Attach:mapuit_screenshot.png]]%0a%0aThe Mapuit Xiao-o wiki is an GNU licensed online information platform for Chinese speaking communities in Europe, it started by creating an information board for abroad studying Chinese students/scholars in the Netherlands, and will gradually move to a Europe-covered information center. %0a%0aThe site covers a wide variety of information including higher education systems(colleges, schools, institutes), tourists(city tourist, site visiting, etc), cultures(festivals, histories) as well as mostly importantly, the students' daily lives(shopping places, administrative procedures, visa application, etc).%0a%0a%0aVisit us at [[http://www.mapuit.com]]%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a[[#mcg]]%0a!!!! [[http://mcg.archi|Marie Christine Gangneux Architect (MCG.archi)]] %25date%25(January 2016)%25%25%0aThis [[http://mcg.archi|MCG.archi]] minimalistic website is a presentation for the French architect and professor Marie Christine Gangneux. It is runs PmWiki with a lightly customized [[Skins/2016]] skin, with galleries showing photos and drawings with [[Cookbook/Mini]] and with [[Cookbook/AutoTOC]] for table of contents. The website is hosted on OVH. (Created and maintained by [[~Petko]].)%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a[[#Matrioszka]]%0a!!!! Matrioszka: O Rosji po polsku ([[http://www.matrioszka.info/|www.matrioszka.info]]) %25date%25(September 2006)%25%25%0a%0a%25lfloat%25 [[http://www.matrioszka.info/|http://www.matrioszka.info/Pliki/MatrioszkaInfo/ZrzutEkranu350.jpg]] %25%25%0a''Matrioszka'' (Polish for «[[Wikipedia:Matryoshka|matryoshka]]») is a website about [[Wikipedia:Russia|Russia]], [[Wikipedia:Russian_language|Russian language]] and culture intended for [[Wikipedia:Poland|Polish]] audience. It is my personal, not-for-profit project I started in 2005 when, after returning from [[Wikipedia:Moscow|Moscow]], I found out that there is no decent source of such information and a niché exists. Originally, I used [[http://www.mamboserver.com/|Mambo]] (now [[http://www.joomla.org/|Joomla]], I suppose) as the CMS backend, which I even ported to [[http://www.postgresql.org/|PostgreSQL]] at that time, but was unsatisfied with the outcome (it worked fine but there was too much hassle with editing -- it's an interface issue).%0a%0aMy goal for ''Matrioszka'' is not just to create a place where I can put some articles I wrote, but rather to provide a platform where other people can write too and be reasonably credited for this. To facilitate editing and increase flexibility I have ported ''Matrioszka'' to [[PmWiki/PmWiki|PmWiki]].%0a%0a'''From the technical side,''' which probably interests you the most, ''Matrioszka'' is not a single website but a [[WikiFarms|WikiFarm]] that also hosts my other sites, ie. [[http://www.piotr.szczepanski.name/|my homepage]], [[http://lwow.piotr.szczepanski.name/|a website]] about [[Wikipedia:Lviv|Lviv]], and some [[http://o.staszic.waw.pl/|other one]] too at the moment, and can be easily extended to more in the future -- it is as simple as issuing an @@mkdir sites/www.example.com/@@ and creating a @@local/config.php@@ in this directory. The site-dependent @@config.php@@ file has virtually just a few lines, as most stuff is configured site-wide in @@farmconfig.php@@, @@extconfig.php@@ (loads extensions, included ''from'' the site @@config.php@@), and @@i18n.LN.php@@ which contains all the language-dependent stuff (@@LN@@ stands for language, currently @@en@@ or @@pl@@).%0a%0aAll of this is possible thanks to [[PmWiki]]'s excellent flexibility (virtually no need to modify the core code, except removing inline CSS and customizing the error message). [[http://httpd.apache.org/|Apache]]'s [[http://httpd.apache.org/docs-2.0/mod/mod_rewrite.html|mod_rewrite]] is also involved. The [[Cookbook:Cookbook|Cookbook]] extensions used are: [[Cookbook:Beautifier|Beautifier]] (not really needed at the moment), [[Cookbook:CommentBoxPlus|CommentBoxPlus]], [[Cookbook:MarkupExtensions|MarkupExtensions]], [[Cookbook:Flash|Flash]] (again, not in use now), [[Cookbook:LinkTitles]], [[Cookbook:MediaCategories|MediaCat]], [[Cookbook:MergeMetaTags|MergeMetaTags]] (disabled for now, not working), [[Cookbook:PageTableOfContents|PageToc]], [[Cookbook:SearchHighLight|SearchHighLight]] (originally not Unicode-clear, but I implemented a lame fix), [[Cookbook:UserAuth|UserAuth]], [[Cookbook:PresenceAwarenessLight|PresenceAwarenessLight]] (turned off for now), [[Cookbook:RandomQuote|RandomQuote]] and [[Cookbook:ViewModes|ViewModes]].%0a%0aI have also rewritten the [[Cookbook:VisitorsLogging1337|VisitorsLogging]] script for use on this page. ''[[~PiotrSzczepanski|Piotr Szczepanski]]''%0a----%0a%0a%25rfloat%25[[http://faculty.valpo.edu/mlundin/mediarevolution|http://faculty.valpo.edu/mlundin/mediarevolution/images/MediaRevolution.png]]%0a%0a'''Media Revolution in Early Modern Europe'''  (http://faculty.valpo.edu/mlundin/mediarevolution)%0a* Course website for college history class on the Print Revolution (Fall 2008)%0a%0aThis is my first use of a wiki in a classroom seeting, and PmWiki has made the experience a breeze. So far, PmWiki (and its eclectic collection of recipes) has enabled me expand the website as classroom needs have changed. Some of the features (and related recipes) include:%0a%0a* A shoutbox ([[Cookbook/Fox]])%0a* A collapsible comment box for quick additions to the site ([[Cookbook/Fox]] and [[Cookbook/Toggle]])%0a* Tag clouds ([[Cookbook/ListCategories]] - allows for organized chaos)%0a* A calendar ([[Cookbook/PmCalendar]])%0a* Multilayered edit and read permissions (via AuthUser)%0a* Embedded flash videos ([[Cookbook/Flash]])%0a* Embedded delicious clouds ([[Cookbook/Delicious]])%0a* Custom links for clipping content to pages (cmsb-addlink.php from [[Cookbook/CMSBundle]])%0a** This is my favorite - there's a scrapbook section on the site in which each page has a link that can be dragged to the bookmark bar and used to clip urls to the page. Thus, students can create their own custom "link dumps."%0a%0aIn short, PmWiki is a complete wiki plus a powerful CMS for classroom contexts. It's far more flexible and robust than the proprietary software offered by many university IT departments.%0a%0aI do hope that the next release of PmWiki will contain built-in blogging tools. To combine the ease of blog content management (and the social networking potential of a blog) with the slow, cumulative growth of a wiki -- now that would be a powerful tool! Wikis are still on the cutting edge -- in many ways, all those fancy Web 2.0 apps are still catching up. But the more PmWiki can be integrated with existing social web tools and methods, the more people will come to see the power of wikis.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#Memofilm]]%0a!!!! memofilm.ru%0ahttp://www.memofilm.ru - russian watched movies dairy with unlimited sorting methods. Content is sorted by itself being used like tags. %0a%0a(July 2013)%0a%0a----%0a[[#Meteobrallo]]%0a%0a!!!! Meteobrallo: (http://www.meteobrallo.com)  %0a%25lfloat%25 [[http://www.meteobrallo.com | http://www.meteobrallo.com/uploads/Main/meteobrallo.jpg]]%0aLinux, embeddedPC & Davis weather stations%0a%0aMeteoBrallo is a dual wiki. First allow to know more information about Brallo di Pregola weather (BdP is a nice italian village). Second describe how to setup  an embedded PC to support and connect to the Internet a weather station using ONLY linux and opensource software. %0a%0a%25date%25(January 2008)%25%25%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a%25lfloat margin-right:10px%25  [[http://mmp-middletown.com/ | http://eclectichosting.net/portfolio/mmp-middletown.com-thumb.jpg]]%0a%0a(:table margin-left=10px border=1 width=30%25 align=right bgcolor=#ccffff cellspacing=0 :)%0a(:cellnr:)%0a'''[[http://eclectictech.net/ | Eclectic Tech site]]'''\\%0a[[~XES | by The Crisses]]%0a(:cellnr:)%0a*Google map%0a*Custom colors on premade template%0a(:tableend:)%0a%0a!!![[http://mmp-middletown.com/ | Minuteman Press, Middletown/Scotchtown, NY]]%0aFrustrated with his franchise-supplied website, Minuteman Press came to Eclectic Tech for a dynamic website that would  fit the corporate colors supplied by the franchise.  Now they can change whatever they want on the website.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a%0a%0a'''Mobilisation Montpellier'''%0a[[http://mobilisation-montpellier.effraie.org/|Site de la mobilisation à l'Université Montpellier 2, contre la LRU et la casse du service public d'enseignement et de recherche en France (printemps 2009)]] This wiki deals with the struggle against the laws destroying the education and the research as a public service in France, this is the local website for the organisation of the struggle in the University of Montpellier 2. the skin is a minor modification of the default skin (recent changes have been put in the sidebar, there is no image,...). By the way, there is a little problem with the french internationalization i18n-fr.zip since the files for PmWikiFr are not in UTF-8, so you will have to use iconv (otherwise the accents are not well displayed).%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a%0a%0a%0a'''MPS Mountaineering'''%0a(http://www.munro-pineapple.org.uk)%0a%0a%25lfloat%25[[http://www.munro-pineapple.org.uk | http://su.nott.ac.uk/~pineappl/pmwiki/uploads/Main/sitethumb.jpg]]%25%25 The website of MPS Mountaineering at Nottingham University.  Having a single webmaster led to a stagnating website, but now everyone in the club contributes to the website, and we have more content updated more regularly than ever before.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a%0a'''Mugen Wiki'''%0a(http://mugen-wiki.info/)%0a%0aA wiki devoted to the 2d fighting game Engine, M.U.G.E.N %0aPmWiki was a huge help. The ability to customize everything makes this the best Wiki software out there.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a!-N-[[#N]]%25center%25%0a----%0a!!!'''NatureVault''' (http://naturevault.org)%0a%0a%25lfloat%25 [[http://www.naturevault.org/wiki/uploads/NatureVault/NatureVault/naturevault.jpg" Understand Nature at NatureVault.org" ->http://naturevault.org]] %0a%0aNatureVault is a collection of knowledge, data, and understanding about how nature works.  It is intended to be resource of alternative information discovered by individuals, not commonly recognized by society, and information which is needed to rebuild society better from a future disaster.  The wiki is fully open source and downloadable in full to preserve in a societal collapse.%0ahttp://naturevault.org%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a!!!'''NetWiki''' (http://netwiki.amath.unc.edu)%0a%0a%25lfloat%25 [[http://netwiki.amath.unc.edu | http://netwiki.amath.unc.edu/netwikipicture.jpg]]%0aNetWiki is a dual-purpose wiki, acting as an open repository of information about network science, including shared codes and data, while also serving as the central online point for some ongoing collaborations applying networks concepts to different problems. It was relatively simple to set up, even with some difficulties navigating details of the server here, while being wonderfully easy to add content to and to maintain, particularly with the wide assortment of cookbooks available.%0ahttp://netwiki.amath.unc.edu%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a----%0a%25lfloat margin-right:10px%25  [[http://newburghenvelope.biz/ | http://eclectichosting.net/portfolio/newburghenvelope.biz-thumb.j